                        </h4></div>
                    <hr>

                    <p>
                        Amydus was looking for ways to grow visitor engagement to their online store after they noticed
                        that their search was not leading to relevant products. Kartik, CEO of Amydus explains “We
                        wanted a search solution that was easy to implement so that our store wouldn’t have to suffer
                        any downtime. The native Magento search was sluggish and mostly gave out irrelevant results to
                        our visitors. We’ve wanted to fix these issues but weren’t able to get anywhere close ourselves
                        due to a lack of expertise and complexity involved in implementing a good search solution.”

                    </p>


                    <div class="post-snippet mb32">

                        <div class="post-title"><h4 class="inline-block">How SearchTap.io helped Amydus

                            </h4></div>
                        <hr>

                    </div>

                    <p>Prior to using SearchTap.io, Kartik tells us that visitors were often complaining about search
                        relevancy issues and painfully slow loading times for search results. Mobile search and
                        navigation experience had poor UX/UI and filters were not user-friendly &amp; responsive. Amydus
                        also had no clue about search specific analytics such as popular searches and zero search result
                        queries that could help them understand their sales funnel.

                    </p>

                    <p>Fed up with the situation, they were actively looking for options. After consulting with
                        SearchTap.io, it became clear to the Amydus team that they would need to use an intelligent
                        e-commerce search solution that could help improve product discovery on their Magento store and
                        take away the pain of painfully slow search load times.
                    </p>

